/PR

/HN/PR

יח וניבא דוע / Our father still lives. This phrase echoes Genesis 45:3 in
which Joseph reveals himself to his brothers and immediately inquires
יח יבא דועה / "Does my father still live?" Josephòs father, Jacob, whose name
was also Israel, is both the physical and spiritual ancestor of the people
Israel. As the last ancestor from whom all Jews are descended, Jacob /
Israel not only represents the Jewish tradition but the living people itself.
As long as the people Israel lives, as long as Judaism remains a vibrant and
dynamic force, Jacobòs spirit continues to live. Our ancestors live on in
us.    /SC/XXR.S./XX/PR

